question:
What is the default port number of HTTP?

A) 21
B) 25
C) 80
D) 443

What happens if you dereference a NULL pointer?

A) Returns 0
B) Returns garbage
C) Runtime error (Segmentation fault)
D) Compilation error

What is pointer arithmetic?

A) Performing arithmetic operations directly on memory addresses as raw byte values

B) Performing arithmetic operations on a pointer where the increment/decrement depends on the size of the data type it points to

C) Adding two pointers to obtain a new valid memory address

D) Changing the value stored at the memory location using arithmetic operators

Which traversal of a binary tree uses recursion naturally?

A) Level Order
B) Breadth First Search
C) Depth First Search
D) Hash Traversal

Which algorithm is used to find the shortest path in a weighted graph with non-negative weights?

A) BFS
B) Dijkstra’s Algorithm
C) DFS
D) Kruskal’s Algorithm

In a complete binary tree with n nodes, the height is approximately:

A) n
B) log n
C) n log n
D) √n
A connected acyclic graph is called a __________.
The memory area used for dynamic allocation is called the __________.
In DBMS, a dependency where a non-prime attribute depends on another non-prime attribute is called __________ dependency.
The memory used by local variables inside a function is stored in the __________ segment.
In hashing with chaining, collisions are handled using a __________.

What is the worst-case time complexity of searching in a hash table (with chaining)?

A) O(1)
B) O(log n)
C) O(n)
D) O(n log n)

What is the time complexity of inserting an element into a binary heap?

A) O(1)
B) O(log n)
C) O(n)
D) O(n log n)

What is the time complexity of BFS traversal of a graph?

A) O(V + E)
B) O(V²)
C) O(E log V)
D) O(V log E)
